description: Megan McNamee  shared  Cynthia Sassi 's  post . This could not be more true. I'm nearing five years of (unexpected) self-employment, and I'm so proud of  Greg McNamee  for what he has created in just a few short months with the  Arizona Door Store . It has its consequences though too. We work all the time (at least he does, and most nights after bedtime for the girls and weekends you'll find us nose to the grindstone). When it's just you the expectation is to always be available, always answer questions, always answer the phone...and that can be hard in so many ways.  I know my other self-employed friends totally relate. It's a bit of a strange world to be in - we do what we love and have lots of control, but the stress and expectations are huge. It's worth it, but man do I support local, small businesses now more than ever knowing how they struggle! Fabulous Arizona
